</LG>
<LG>
<L>FAR-DISTANT Tibet in her gloomy woods</L>
<L>Rears the gay tent, of blended wool unwov'n,</L>
<L>And glutinous materials: the Chin$&s;e</L>
<L>Their porcelain, Japan its varni&s;h boa&s;ts.</L>
<L>Some fair peculiar graces ev'ry realm,</L>
<L>And each from each a &s;hare of wealth acquires.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>BUT chief by numbers of indu&s;trious hands</L>
<L>A nation's wealth is counted: numbers rai&s;e</L>
<L>Warm emulation: where that virtue dwells,</L>
<L>There will be traffic's &s;eat; there will &s;he build</L>
<L>Her rich emporium. Hence, ye happy &s;wains,</L>
<L>With ho&s;pitality inflame your brea&s;t,</L>
<L>And emulation: the whole world receive,</L>
<L>And with their arts, their virtues, deck your i&s;le.</L>
<L>Each clime, each &s;ea, the &s;pacious orb of each,</L>
<L N="540">Shall join their various &s;tores, and amply fe$d</L>
<L>The mighty brotherhood; while ye proceed,</L>
<L>Active and enterpri&s;ing, or to teach</L>
<L>The &s;tream a naval cour&s;e, or till the wild,</L>
<L>Or drain the fen, or &s;tretch the long canal,</L>
<L>Or plough the fertile billows of the d$$p.</L>
<L>Why to the narrow circle of our coa&s;t</L>
<L>Should we &s;ubmit our limits, while each wind</L>
<L>A&s;&s;i&s;ts the &s;tream and &s;ail, and the wide main</L>
<L>Wooes us in ev'ry port? Se$ Belgium build,</L>
<L N="550"><PB N="84" REF="87">
