<L>From Ezion-geber, pa&s;s'd th' Arabian gulph.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L N="160">BUT later times, more fortunate, have found,</L>
<L>O'er ocean's open wave, a &s;urer cour&s;e,</L>
<L>Sailing the we&s;tern coa&s;t of Afric's realms,</L>
<L>Of Mauritania, and Nigritian tracts,</L>
<L>And i&s;lands of the Gorgades, the bounds,</L>
<L>On the Atlantic brine, of ancient trade;</L>
<L>But not of modern, by the virtue led</L>
